            <person xml:id="pers1496">
               <p>A stonemason from <placeName>Birstall</placeName>, <persName>Mason</persName>
                  heard <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> preach while
                  working on buildings in <placeName>Moorfields, London</placeName> in <date
                     when="1739">1739</date>, and was converted. On his return home he became an
                  evangelist in the area around <placeName>Birstall</placeName>. In <date
                     when="1742">1742</date>
                  <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName> enrolled him as a
                  regular <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> and he remained under
                  appointment until his death. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 295–98;
                     <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 817–18; <hi rend="italic">EMP</hi> 1:1–178; and
                  Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 250.</p>
            </person>
